.TH "nfc_data_exchange" 9 "nfc_data_exchange" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfc_data_exchange \- transceive data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nfc_data_exchange
.BI "(struct nfc_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "u32 target_idx "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "data_exchange_cb_t cb "  ","
.BI "void *cb_context "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
The nfc device that found the target
.IP "target_idx" 12
index of the target
.IP "skb" 12
data to be sent
.IP "cb" 12
callback called when the response is received
.IP "cb_context" 12
parameter for the callback function
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The user must wait for the callback before calling this function again.
